  <description type="morphology">Subshrubs or shrubs, 2–10 × 3–10 dm. Leaves cauline 1/2 or more length of flowering stem; petiole 0.5–1 cm; blade lanceolate to oblanceolate or elliptic, 1–4 × 0.5–1.5 cm, usually densely tomentose on both surfaces, sometimes floccose and greenish adaxially. Inflorescences 3–10 cm; branches tomentose to floccose. Involucres 1–2 × 1–1.5(–2) mm. Flowers 1.5–2.5 mm; perianth usually pale yellow to yellow, sometimes white, glabrous. 2n = 40.</description>
